"Pours clear medium amber, producing slightly over a finger of beige, mostly finely bubbled but shortlived head that leaves no lace. Aroma is sweet caramel & roasted malts, heavy pumpkin pie spices & some vegetable pumpkin. Like many pumpkin ales the spices are so heavy that the more subtle aromas are somewhat subdued. Taste is thinner than the nose & is a little watery for my taste but has more malt roast than sweet caramel; cinnamon, ginger & other pumpkin pie spices stand out with low pumpkin presence. All flavors are present throughout the sip & there is a definite hop spiciness in the finish that bleeds over as a light bitterness in the dry, cinnamon & ginger aftertaste. Light-medium bodied with low carbonation, thin on the tongue & dry with a spicy prickle."
"I have an almost irrational distaste for this brewery but this is a solid pumpkin beer. Not overly spiced, has an appealing sweetness with a dry finish, medium bodied, crisp carbonation, easy drinking. Nothing at all offensive here except perhaps the label (surprise surprise). You could do a lot worse in a pumpkin beer."
"Slightly hazy orange amber color. Spice and light sugary maltiness. Tick."
