"maybe not the most unique and compelling pumpkin beer here from magic hat, but a solid sixer of fall beer nevertheless. its got a rich autumnal copper color and definitely looks the part. the nose shows a lot more spice than pumpkin, but dont they all? spices seem well rounded, appropriately selected and dosed, and not so dominant as to limit drinkability. pumpkin flavor is minimal here, very little real squash character, but the pie spices bring me where i think the beer is meant to take me, and it seems fally enough for me. carbonation is a touch low, as is the body. i like a little more meat on my fall seasonals, and even though its still only august, i was left looking for a bit more substance. a league below the best examples of the style, but a serviceable brew just the same."
